What are state variables?
these are variables that represent data tha t belongs to a compoennt
and can change during its lifecycle. State variables are preserved
by React between renders. Thye allow you to store information like
user input, component status, or any data that  needs to change dramatically.

What is a setter fuction?
They update the state and trigger a re-render of the component. when you 
call a setter function with a new value, react rememberes that new 
value and re-renders the component with the updated state. 

