Why shoul dwe use expo and react native?

React Native is an excellent choice when we need to:

develop apps for both Android and iOS using a unified codebase
leverage existing JavaScript/React skills
achieve near-native performance with shorter development cycles
build scalable apps
Expo adds additional benefits by:

eliminating the need for Xcode/Android Studio configuration
providing access to a broad set of prebuilt native modules via the Expo SDK
offering easy testing on physical devices
simplifying the build and deployment process
enabling instant Over-the-Air updates with EAS Update, delivering changes to users in seconds
supporting integration with custom native build pipelines when needed

React Native has become a mature solution for cross-platform development, with a large ecosystem of libraries and strong community support. Expo enhances this ecosystem by providing curated, tested modules and streamlined tooling that work seamlessly together. We highly recommend using Expo when getting started with React Native. It simplifies setup, accelerates development, and covers most use cases without needing native code changes.
